result.execSummary:
The defendant Latonia C Davis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law. Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

As to Count 1 as amended:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 MONTHS at the House of Corrections CONCURRENT to Count 2 on the Amended Information.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 18 MONTHS probation.


As to Count 2 as added on the Amended Information:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 3 MONTHS at the House of Corrections CONCURRENT to Count 1 as amended.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 18 MONTHS probation.


  Conditions of Probation:
-Complete a parenting class
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department
- Mental health assessment and cooperate with any programs/treatment/counseling deemed necessary by the probation department
-No VIOLENT contact with the children

Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief

As to both counts listed on the Amended Information,   Defendant changes her plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Defendant Latonia C Davis in court with attorney Alejandro A. Lockwood.  Sarah Zwach, student intern, under the supervision of Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Filed, original amended information; copy served on defendant.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of information, waives formal reading, pleads not guilty.  
Court ordered Count 1 amended to Misdemeanor Battery, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.19(1)and 939.51(3)(a), a Class A  Misdemeanor.
The Amended Information added Count 2, Disorderly Conduct, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 947.01(1) and 939.51(3)(b), a Class B Misdemeanor.
